<subSubSection id="C3086569FFBAFF9FE1AF241DB9E5F886" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAD36E2FFBAFF9FE1AF241DB9E5F886" blockId="22.[151,1437,984,1914]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
<materialsCitation id="3B7A3CBFFFBAFF9FE1AF241DB9E5F886" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1499315579" collectionCode="MfN" country="Peru" county="Figs" location="For" municipality="Furthermore" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Huanuco" typeStatus="lectotype">
<emphasis id="B966EAF0FFBAFF9FE1AF241DBB46F982" bold="true" box="[199,315,1637,1662]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Remarks.</emphasis>
We found some variation in the size of the iridescent patch on both the male and female hind wings (compare 
<figureCitation id="13292A67FFBAFF9FE06F24F1BB30F95E" box="[263,333,1673,1698]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1555,1577]" captionTargetBox="[237,1357,224,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[187,1423,197,1528]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 9. Adults in dorsal and ventral views. Taxon names appear below each set. Bia peruana: a, male, Peru, Pasco, Chuchurras (NHMUK); b, female, Peru, Pasco, Chuchurras (FLMNH); c, male, Peru, Pasco, Pachitea (MfN); d, female, Peru, Pasco, Pachitea (NHMUK); e, male, Peru, Ucayali, Pucallpa (ZSM). Intermediate between rebeli and peruana: f, male, Peru, Ucayali, Jepelacio (NHMUK)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/569739/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
<collectingCounty id="62CC4E6EFFBAFF9FE06F24F1BB4AF95E" box="[263,311,1673,1698]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Figs</collectingCounty>
9
</figureCitation>
a, c and e; and also 9b and d). 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BC9AC98FFBAFF9FE3F524F1B951F95E" box="[669,812,1673,1698]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Furthermore</collectingMunicipality>
, some specimens have color patterns that might suggest some interspecific hybridization. 
<location id="8ECD6039FFBAFF9FE37024D7B842F93A" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03BB87F4FFBAFF9FE1FF2115B9E5F886:8ECD6039FFBAFF9FE37024D7B842F93A" box="[536,575,1711,1734]" country="Peru" county="Figs" municipality="Furthermore" name="For" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" stateProvince="Huanuco">For</location>
example, unlike the typical 
<taxonomicName id="4C124D61FFBAFF9FE2E524D7B997F93A" box="[909,1002,1711,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruana">
<emphasis id="B966EAF0FFBAFF9FE2E524D7B997F93A" box="[909,1002,1711,1734]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">peruana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the specimen in 
